SD=Loan
CR= Loan Fulfillment Arrangement
BQs=Interest ServiceFees Disbursement Maintenance Withdrawal Repayment Restructuring
The loan product represents a generic loan capability that may include different properties/features depending on a bank's preferences and policies. The loan may or may not be secured by collateral.
Example of use: An established and valued bank customer applies for and gets a loan for a home improvement project
This service domain handles the fulfillment of a general loan product. This includes the initial set-up of the loan facility and the completion of scheduled and ad-hoc product processing tasks
CR - Loan Fulfillment Arrangement				BQ 1 - Interest	BQ 2 - Service Fees		BQ 3 - Disbursement	BQ 4 - Maintenance		BQ 5 - Withdrawal				BQ 6 - Repayment				BQ 7 - Restructuring				
In	Up	Co	Re	Re	Ex	Re	Re	Rq	Re	Up	Ex	Rq	Re	Up	Ex	Rq	Re	In	Up	Ec	Rq	Re
InCR Initiate a loan
UpCR Update details for an existing loan
CoCR Control a loan (e.g. suspend, terminate)
ReCR Retrieve details about a loan
ReBQ Retrieve details about interest applied to a loan
ExBQ Execute a fee charge against a loan
ReBQ Retrieve details about a loan fees
ReBQ Retrieve details about a disbursement paid against a loan
RqBQ Request a maintenance activity for a consumer load (e.g. obtain a fee statement)
ReBQ Retrieve details about maintenance processing for a loan
UpBQ Update details of a withdrawal from a loan
ExBQ Execute an automated withdrawal against a loan
RqBQ Request handling of a withdrawal (e.g. negotiate an exception)
ReBQ Retrieve details about a loan withdrawal
UpBQ Update a repayment transaction made to the loan
ExBQ Execute an automated repayment transaction
RqBQ Request handling of an exceptional repayment (e.g. a balloon repayment)
ReBQ Retrieve details about a loan repayment
InBQ Initiate loan account restructuring
UpBQ Update details of a loan or restructuring activities
EcBQ Accept, reject etc a loan restructuring proposal
RqBQ Request activity associated with a restructuring effort (e.g. negotiate)
ReBQ Retrieve details about a loan restructuring task